The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Infosys has invested Australian $1.9 million in cash and services for a research programme to help Australias services sector create more intellectual property. Smart Services Co-operative Research Centre is a $120-million research collaboration between 12 industry participants, six leading universities and the Federal and Queensland governments to develop the research and development programme. The initial focus of the programme will be to create intellectual property for finance, media and government sectors.                            
	 Reliance Money has forayed into wealth management as part of its expansion plan. The company plans to create a separate financial planning unit for senior citizens. The wealth management platform will include tax planning and assessment, real estate, art advisory and estate planning.                            
	 BSEL Infrastructure has reported a 144 per cent rise in consolidated net sales at Rs 374.20 crore for the year ended March 31, 2008, against Rs 153.23 crore last year. The profit after tax for the year stood at Rs 112.08 crore, a rise of 45.7 per cent from Rs 76.92 crore in the previous fiscal.                            
	 Syndicate Bank has raised interest rates on deposits to 90 basis points with effect from July 2, 2008. The bank has also revised the benchmark prime lending rate from 13 per cent to 13.50 per cent.                             
	 Corporation Bank has launched Corp Compassion  a savings bank account. The bank will donate Rs 10 for the underprivileged children for every account opened under Corp Compassion. The bank has set a target of acquiring one million new customers during the campaign period.                            
	 The Uco Bank has recorded a total business of Rs 1,35,536 crore with a net profit of Rs 412 crore during the year ended March 31, 2008.                             
	 ICSA (India) Ltd has received a contract worth Rs 145.91 crore from various state electricity boards for the supply of 132KV, 33/11KV and 11KV substations and lines and for the building, testing and commissioning of high and low tension distribution transformers.                             
	 The sales turnover of Richa Knits Ltd increased 56 per cent to Rs 100 crore from Rs 63 crore in the financial year 2007-08. The profit after tax rose to Rs 7 crore from Rs 3 crore and the earnings per share was Rs 4.27.                            
	 Vodafone Essar launched a range of bonus cards comprising STD bonus cards at Rs 74, SMS bonus cards at Rs 51 and local bonus cards at Rs 42 with 30-days tariff validity.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
